  "prompt": "How can I retain downvoted question in Quora?",
  "response": "Here are a few strategies to help retain or improve a downvoted Quora question:\n\n1. Revise the question\n- Improve clarity\n- Make it more specific\n- Use proper grammar and punctuation\n- Ensure it follows Quora's guidelines\n\n2. Analyze the reason for downvotes\n- Check comments for feedback\n- Understand why users found the question unhelpful\n- Address potential issues in your original question\n\n3. Edit the question\n- Rephrase the content\n- Add more context\n- Make it more engaging\n- Provide additional details\n\n4. Repost with modifications\n- Wait for some time before reposting\n- Substantially change the question's structure\n- Incorporate previous feedback\n\n5. Seek community feedback\n- Ask Quora users for suggestions\n- Request guidance on improving the question\n- Be open to constructive criticism\n\n6. Check question quality\n- Ensure the question is unique\n- Avoid repetitive or previously answered queries\n- Make it informative and interesting\n\n7. Use appropriate tags\n- Select relevant and precise topic tags\n- Help the right audience find your question\n\n8. Be patient\n- Sometimes questions take time to gain traction\n- Don't delete immediately after receiving downvotes\n\nRemember, maintaining quality and following community guidelines is key to retaining and improving your Quora question.",
